Careers





















Careers

Compensation and BenefitsLearning and DevelopmentRecruitmentJob Openings















Home> Careers




Opportunity. Community. Unity. The Vulcan way of business is a great way to build your career.  
At Vulcan, we invest in our people, giving the essential training, guidance and supportive environment they need to develop, advance and excel. In other words, we look for ways to let our people shine. 








Essential Opportunities We recognize that success in all of our activities is related directly to the talents, dedication and performance of the people who work here.  Vulcan employs approximately 7,000 people across the United States, Mexico and the Bahamas. We are continually looking for talented, motivated men and women who want to join our team. Our employment opportunities are broad, ranging from engineering to human resources. Our common goal is to find the best person for the job. Whether you’re looking to make a strategic career move or a new college graduate looking to start your career, our Job Openings offer great opportunities. 











Our Work Environment Our people share a competitive drive for excellence, in an environment of trust, teamwork, positive reinforcement, open-mindedness and communication. Ours is a culture of mutual respect, integrity and committed spirit. At Vulcan, you will find a sense of community whether you work at our corporate headquarters, in one of our divisions, or at any of the hundreds of site operations located from California to the East Coast and from Illinois to Florida to the Yucatán Peninsula of Mexico. Community runs deep here. As a business, we believe in being a good neighbor, and our employees participate in many charitable activities, such as volunteering in local schools, working on Habitat for Humanity projects, helping adults learn to read, working at food banks, or volunteering for a number of local and national service organizations in activities that help make our communities stronger. 








OPEN ALL [+]
CLOSE ALL [-]




Competencies We Seek

Open [+]





We look for individuals who share our commitment to excellence and exhibit high standards of personal and business integrity. Core competencies we seek to hire and develop include commitment to the team, dependability, problem-solving skills, resourcefulness, traits of leadership and the ability to set and meet challenging goals. A sampling of the job opportunities Vulcan offers includes:  Engineering:  Civil, Electrical, Environmental, Mechanical and Mining Finance, Accounting and Auditing Geology Human Resources Information Technology Marketing, Sales and Market Research Occupational Health and Safety Operations and Production Management 






Drug-Free Workplace

Open [+]





Vulcan is committed to providing a drug-free work environment, and the Company’s policies, procedures, and practices reflect that commitment.






Recruiting/Staffing Firms and Agencies

Open [+]





It is Vulcan policy not to accept resumes from recruiting/staffing firms and agencies that have not signed our vendor agreement. Even if we have a vendor agreement with such a firm, we will not accept resumes and will consider them unsolicited unless Vulcan has specifically requested assistance filling a specific position. If resumes are received unsolicited by Vulcan, they will be considered the property of Vulcan Materials Company. Any recruiting/staffing firm or agency wishing to do business with Vulcan must contact us at recruiting@vmcmail.com. Recruiting/staffing firms may NOT contact hiring managers directly.






Fair Employment Policy

Open [+]





SCOPE: This policy applies to all employees of Vulcan Materials Company and its subsidiaries. GENERAL STATEMENT: It is the policy of Vulcan Materials Company to recruit and promote persons on the basis of demonstrated merit and provide a working environment free from illegal discrimination in any form. Vulcan respects the dignity of its job candidates and employees and deals with them on the basis of their individual merit. The continued success of Vulcan Materials Company is contingent upon hiring and retaining qualified employees without unlawful discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law from discrimination. To achieve this end, we reaffirm our policy: POLICY:  Vulcan will recruit, employ, train, and promote persons in all job categories without unlawful discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by law from discrimination. In accordance with applicable laws and executive orders, Vulcan shall administer its affirmative action plans to achieve the employment of qualified individuals. All employment decisions will be made with commitment to the principles of both merit selection and equal employment opportunity. All human resource actions, including but not limited to, job opportunities, compensation, transfers, layoffs, recalls, training, education, tuition assistance, social and recreational programs and disciplinary measures will be administered without unlawful discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law from discrimination, except where a safety or health hazard or a bona fide occupational qualification would limit such human resource action. Vulcan strongly disapproves of and will not condone illegal discrimination in any form, including unlawful harassment, which is defined in Corporate Policy No. ER-15 and Corporate Policy No. ER-16. Vulcan will continue to maintain employee performance standards at a high level consistent with job requirements. Any employee or applicant for employment who believes that he or she has been unlawfully discriminated against by reason of his or her race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law from discrimination or has been subjected to unlawful harassment should report his or her complaint to a human resources official of their choice or report it by accessing the Company’s Helpline at 1-800-615-4331 or via the internet at www.vulcanmaterials.com. Unlawful retaliatory action against an employee because the employee has participated in any investigation or has filed a complaint pursuant to this policy will not be tolerated. This policy is not intended and shall not be construed or interpreted to unlawfully discriminate against any individual employee or applicant by reason of his or her race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by law from discrimination. Any manager having a reason to believe unlawful discrimination or harassment exists or having knowledge of any occurrences of such discrimination must report this information immediately to the human resources director of the region or office involved. The Company’s Senior Vice President of Human Resources, in coordination with Region Human Resources Directors, is responsible for implementing and monitoring this policy. 






EMPLOYMENT VERIFICATIONS

Open [+]





Vulcan Materials Company uses The Work Number to provide automated employment and income verifications on our employees.  1-800-367-5690 or www.theworknumber.com  Vulcan Materials Company Employer Code: 15463









If you need assistance applying for a current open position, please call the Vulcan Materials Company Career Line at (205) 298-3175  and leave a message requesting assistance or email your request to taleosupport@vmcmail.com. If you do not require help to apply for a current open position, please apply by clicking on employment opportunities and follow the online application process.




















